ğŸ“ Background
A private training institute conducts multiple short-term technology courses
(e.g., Java, Spring, Database, Web Development).

Until now, student records were stored manually in notebooks.
This caused:

Duplicate student IDs

Lost records

No easy way to search or display data

The institute wants a simple Java console application that:

Works offline

Stores data permanently in a file

Follows clean layered architecture (MVC)

ğŸ¯ BUSINESS REQUIREMENTS
The system must:

Register students with unique student IDs

Store student data persistently in a file

Display all registered students

Prevent duplicate student registrations

Be easy to maintain and extend

Use good OOP and design practices

ğŸ“˜ FUNCTIONAL USE CASES
Use Case	       Description
Add Student	       Register a new student
View Students	   Display all students
Exit System	Safely terminate program
